<p>I'm just starting out with Angular.</p>  <p>I've written some code that downloads a JSON array <code>configuredAPIs</code> and displays each object within it, <code>&lt;div ng-repeat="capi in configuredAPIs"&gt;</code>.   For each of these, there's another directive to list the items from an array of strings, <code>&lt;tr ng-repeat="eurl in capi.externalURLs"&gt;</code></p>  <p>Underneath there's a text box to add a new string to this array, which I've bound to a <code>$scope</code> variable called <code>url</code>.</p>  <p>When I click the 'add' button, everything works - the new string is added to the array, a new row appears in the table.. ..but it only works once.  Subsequent clicks on the 'add' button add empty strings to the array (and thus empty text boxes).</p>  <p>What have I done wrong?</p>  <p><strong>index.html</strong></p>  <pre><code>    &lt;div ng-app="testApp" ng-controller="testCtrl"&gt;          &lt;div ng-repeat="capi in configuredAPIs"&gt;              &lt;h1&gt;Configured API&lt;/h1&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Name:                 {{ capi.name }}             &lt;/p&gt;               &lt;h2&gt;External URLs&lt;/h2&gt;             &lt;form ng-submit="addExternalURL(capi)"&gt;                 &lt;table&gt;                     &lt;!-- A row in the table for each string in the array --&gt;                     &lt;tr ng-repeat="eurl in capi.externalURLs"&gt;                         &lt;td&gt;                             &lt;input type="text" ng-model="eurl" /&gt;                         &lt;/td&gt;                     &lt;/tr&gt;                      &lt;!-- Final table row to add a new string to the array --&gt;                     &lt;tr&gt;                         &lt;td&gt;                             &lt;input type="text" ng-model="url" placeholder="Enter a new external URL"&gt;                             &lt;input class="btn-primary" type="submit" value="add"&gt;                         &lt;/td&gt;                     &lt;/tr&gt;                 &lt;/table&gt;             &lt;/form&gt;          &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p><strong>controller.js</strong></p>  <pre><code>var app = angular.module('testApp', []); app.controller('testCtrl', function ($scope, $http) {      $scope.url = 'new url';      $http.get("/api/configuredapis?orgid=2")     .success(function (response) { $scope.configuredAPIs = response; });      $scope.addExternalURL = function ($capi) {         $capi.externalURLs.push($scope.url);         $scope.url = '';     };  }); </code></pre>